<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Tales of Phantasia on BJ3M?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12361&amp;p=140897#p140897"><![CDATA[
Mine is done this way:<br />-MAD-1 (pin #13, chip only) goes to SNES CON. pin #48<br />-MAD-1 (pin #12) goes to SNES CON. pin #47<br />-A21 (first ROM) goes to SNES CON. pin #46<br /><br />Also keep in mind that Tales of Phantasia is an EXHIROM game and thus /OE of the first and second ROM have to be swapped together on MAD-1. I mean if you have a game with 2 different ROM chips, you usually connect /OE of the first ROM to MAD-1 pin #16 and the /OE of 2nd ROM, you connect it to MAD-1 pin #01 but for EXHIROM games it is swapped, I mean you have to connect /OE P0 to MAD-1 pin #01 and /OE P1 to MAD-1 pin #16. I have no idea why that is but it is done this way and it works only this way<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3986">MaarioS</a> — Mon Feb 09, 2015 11:46 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
